sentences: Scott Boerma (born 1964) is a composer of contemporary classical music, an arranger of music for marching ensembles, and the Director of Bands at Western Michigan University.
Before those positions, Boerma was Director of Bands at Eastern Michigan University, and he began his career teaching music in the Michigan public schools at Novi and Lamphere High Schools.
Boerma has also studied composition with Anthony Iannaccone at Eastern Michigan University.
He is commissioned each year by high school, university and community bands to write new works for the repertoire.
From 1989-2006 and from 2014-2018, he was the music arranger for the top-ranking Madison Scouts Drum & Bugle Corps.
